  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Maintenance Engineer (Equipment / Automation / Mechanical)",
  "description": "<p>Job Description:</p><p><strong>1. Equipment Maintenance:</strong></p><ul><li>Perform regular maintenance and calibration of equipment to ensure optimal functionality, particularly for Infineon project requirements.</li><li>Develop and implement preventive maintenance schedules to minimize downtime.</li></ul><p><strong>2. Mechanical Troubleshooting:</strong></p><ul><li>Diagnose and resolve mechanical issues promptly to prevent production delays in the Infineon project.</li><li>Use technical manuals, schematics, and diagnostic tools to identify problems.</li></ul><p><strong>3. On-Duty Business:</strong></p><ul><li>Serve as the primary point of contact for Infineon customers regarding quality issues.</li><li>Ensure timely and effective communication with Infineon customers to address their concerns.</li><li>Document and report on quality incidents, providing detailed analysis and solutions.</li></ul><p><strong>4. PLC Skills:</strong></p><ul><li>Utilize PLC (Programmable Logic Controller) skills to program, troubleshoot, and maintain automated systems specific to Infineon project requirements.</li><li>Ensure that PLC systems are functioning correctly and efficiently.</li><li>Provide training and support to team members on PLC operations and best practices.</li></ul><p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor's degree in Mechanical Engineering, Electrical Engineering, or a related field.</li><li>Proven experience in equipment maintenance and mechanical troubleshooting.</li><li>Strong knowledge of PLC programming and troubleshooting.</li><li>Excellent problem-solving and analytical skills.</li><li>Effective communication and customer service skills.</li><li>Ability to work independently and as part of a team.</li><li>Willingness to travel to Infineon customer sites as needed.</li></ul>",
